spla
------------------------------------------
SPLA provides specialized functions for linear algebra computations with a C++
and C interface, which are inspired by requirements in computational material
science codes.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.1.6-1
  libgcc1-9.3.0-2
  libgomp1-9.3.0-2
  libopenblas-0.3.10-1
  libopenmpi40-3.1.6-1
  libspla-devel-1.0.0-1bl1
  libspla0-1.0.0-1bl1
  libstdc++6-9.3.0-2
  pkg-config-1.6.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.34+1git.de9c1b7cfe-1
  cmake-3.17.3-2
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-9.3.0-2
  gcc-g++-9.3.0-2
  ninja-1.10.0-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/eth-cscs/spla

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/eth-cscs/spla/archive/v1.0.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack spla-1.0.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./spla-1.0.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/spla-1.0.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/spla-1.0.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libspla0-1.0.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libspla-devel-1.0.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(spla)
